<h1><span id="Modern_Defense">Modern Defense</span></h1>
<p>The Modern or Robatsch Defense. Black makes clear intentions to fianchetto a Bishop. Black firmly embraces the hypermodern approach of controlling the center from the sides. The Bishop can quickly take the strong diagonal a1-h8, and also provide some defense for the King if castling on this side.
</p><p>Moves:
</p>
<dl><dd>2. d4</dd>
<dd>2. Nf3</dd>
<dd>2. f4</dd></dl><p>White has also the possibility to launch a quick attack on the f7 pawn by the means of 2. Bc4 and Qf3.
</p>
